# Rules

**0. Follow Discord’s policies.**
You must follow the Discord Community Guidelines.

**1. Be respectful.**
No personal insults, harassment, or attacks on anyone’s character, appearance, identity, or background. No discrimination or hate speech of any kind.

**2. Debate ideas, not people.**
Attack arguments, not arguers. Disagree as much as you like — but keep it about the topic, not the person holding the view.

**3. Assume good faith & seek clarity.**
If you’re confused, ask for clarification. If someone asks you to clarify, assume good faith and answer. Clear up misunderstandings early instead of letting them fester.

**4. Stay on topic & use the right channels.**
Keep conversations relevant to the channel you’re in. If a Steward/Moderator asks you to move a discussion, please do so. For new channel ideas, use #drs-discord-meta.

**5. Focus on quality & sources.**
Prefer primary sources (filings, regulations, SRO docs, etc.) over screenshots and hearsay. Share links and explain your reasoning when you can. If you’re sharing a theory, 
label it as a theory — don’t present speculation as proven fact.

**6. No doxxing or unsafe behavior.**
Don’t share anyone’s private information (yours or others’). Don’t encourage or organize illegal or clearly harmful activity. This server is for education and discussion, 
not personalized financial, legal, or tax advice.

**7. Limit self-promotion.**
No unsolicited ads, recruiting, or DMs for your project, channel, fund, etc. Use the designated self-promotion channels if/when they exist.

**8. Good-faith participation only.**
If your behavior consistently drags conversations into bad faith (concern trolling, rule-lawyering, endless drama, scab picking, etc.), moderation will step in even if you’re technically 
within the letter of the rules. Ban evasion, coordinated harassment, raid behavior, or use of alternate accounts to bypass moderation may result in immediate removal. 
